main event: A bright, circular flying object was observed moving at a high rate of speed on the night of September 27, 1954.
interesting points: The sighting involved a circular object moving southwest at high speeds between 12,000 and 15,000 feet,The object was observed for approximately four minutes by Capt. P. Swift,The observation was made while en route from Washington D.C. to Newark, N.J.,The conclusion of the report was that there was insufficient data for evaluation,The report included a reference to potential V/c observation.
witness description: Capt. P. Swift, pilot of a Martin 4240 type aircraft
